{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require companies to report on Environment, Social and Governance factors",
        "additional_details": "Greater monitoring and transparency is needed so that UK businesses are accountable for their impact on the environment, their contribution to their local communities, how they promote diversity and workforce wellbeing, how they are governed and how they conduct their business day-to-day.\r\n \r\nEnvironmental impact of businesses should be top of the agenda for the future of this world.",
        "background": "The Government should amend Company Law to include provision for non-financial reporting by UK businesses, with mandatory reporting of Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) factors.",
